	     Johannesburg – A 14-year-old girl was seriously injured when a car knocked her over after she got off a school bus in Germiston on Wednesday morning, paramedics said.  The driver of the car carried her into the school before paramedics arrived, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement. She sustained a serious injury to her leg. She was given pain-relief medication and taken to Themba Memorial Hospital.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  